37:54.180 --> 37:55.932
Who you care about.

37:56.810 --> 37:58.892
And then I will go to work on them.

38:00.650 --> 38:01.810
Mom...

38:02.730 --> 38:03.890
Dad...

38:05.070 --> 38:06.105
wife...

38:07.490 --> 38:08.605
kids...

38:09.450 --> 38:13.443
And when they ask me why I am doing
these awful things to them,

38:14.660 --> 38:16.070
I will tell them,

38:16.540 --> 38:20.032
"Because Danilo chose the Americans
over you."

40:47.940 --> 40:50.932
That's half the Brownsville
Sheriff's Department.

40:51.530 --> 40:53.066
Off duty, of course.

40:55.410 --> 40:58.527
-He's a very popular man.
-He is.

40:59.240 --> 41:01.492
He has the respect and love of his people.

41:01.580 --> 41:02.899
And their obedience.

41:03.290 --> 41:04.746
I'm Juan brego.

41:06.710 --> 41:07.950
The nephew.

41:10.250 --> 41:12.161
-I've heard of you.
-Rea|ly?

41:12.260 --> 41:15.377
-Yeah.
-And I've heard of you. Of course.

41:16.970 --> 41:18.540
Are you enjoying the party?

41:19.760 --> 41:21.637
I didn't come here for a party.

41:22.020 --> 41:24.341
I came to talk business with your uncle.

41:24.440 --> 41:25.475
Yes.

41:26.440 --> 41:29.352
You came to try to convince my uncle
to get into cocaine.

41:31.030 --> 41:34.852
My uncle is an opium trafficker.
A lot of years in that game.

41:34.950 --> 41:37.316
And for good reason.

41:38.200 --> 41:41.158
He knows that product is safe for us.

41:41.290 --> 41:43.076
We grow it.

41:43.290 --> 41:45.576
Harvest it. Control it.

41:45.830 --> 41:48.287
No Colombians to deal with.

41:48.380 --> 41:50.336
No airplanes through Honduras.

41:50.420 --> 41:54.459
But more importantly... no headlines.

41:56.800 --> 41:58.791
Cocaine scares America.

41:59.720 --> 42:03.349
And my uncle wants to keep
his American friends.

42:03.720 --> 42:07.224
So convincing my uncle won't be easy.

42:09.690 --> 42:11.066
And you? What do you think?

42:11.320 --> 42:14.608
I think there is only one reason
not to get into cocaine.

42:18.070 --> 42:19.025
You.

42:22.030 --> 42:24.863
Stop the music for a moment.

42:25.410 --> 42:31.497
The local children's choir has prepared
a song in gratitude for Juan Guerra.

42:31.840 --> 42:33.546
Go ahead, children.

43:29.850 --> 43:31.727
They even sing in English.

46:41.290 --> 46:44.509
And here is the guest of honor.

46:45.630 --> 46:48.713
I think you're always
the guest of honor here.

46:49.180 --> 46:50.169
Sure.

46:51.600 --> 46:53.056
Do you know why?

46:54.770 --> 46:58.934
Because I've been doing this a long time.

47:00.190 --> 47:02.818
What we've built here in the east
is nowhere near what you've built

47:02.900 --> 47:04.185
in the rest of the country.

47:05.440 --> 47:08.068
But it has all that I need.

47:09.450 --> 47:10.815
And none of what I don't.

47:12.160 --> 47:15.323
What you're asking of me, of my people...

47:16.500 --> 47:18.240
is a big deal.

47:20.670 --> 47:22.535
We aren't barbarians.

47:23.960 --> 47:25.086
I know that.

47:26.420 --> 47:27.705
That's why I'm here.

47:28.420 --> 47:29.796
Look, Miguel ngel,

47:30.130 --> 47:32.587
the opium business has been good to us.

47:33.640 --> 47:37.804
Lots of profits and reliable users
in the States.

47:38.060 --> 47:39.345
Most of them "undesirables."

47:40.390 --> 47:41.516
Blacks.

47:42.860 --> 47:44.475
Former soldiers.

47:46.020 --> 47:48.352
People the government
doesn't give a shit about.

47:49.990 --> 47:53.812
It makes it easier for the Americans
to look the other way.

47:55.370 --> 47:56.860
But cocaine?

47:57.290 --> 47:59.861
What? Scares the Americans?

48:01.290 --> 48:02.917
That's bullshit.

48:03.000 --> 48:05.628
What scares the Americans
IS how much they love It.

48:06.130 --> 48:08.086
They're obsessed with that shit.

48:08.420 --> 48:10.718
America will get its cocaine.

48:11.050 --> 48:14.338
One way or another.
Better that it's through us.

48:14.970 --> 48:15.925
Us?

48:17.060 --> 48:18.129
Us?

48:20.520 --> 48:22.385
My nephew likes cocaine.

48:22.480 --> 48:26.644
He doesn't care that famous people
are killing themselves on it.

48:26.820 --> 48:29.892
He likes the margins, you know?
How can you not?

48:31.860 --> 48:35.318
But do you know why we never got into it?

48:35.780 --> 48:37.691
Because of people like you.

48:39.200 --> 48:43.318
We saw what you did to your partners,
let alone your competitors.

48:44.750 --> 48:46.741
And now you're inviting us in?

48:47.880 --> 48:50.371
So I have to ask myself,
"Why am I so luclq?"

48:53.720 --> 48:55.836
A white storm is coming.

48:56.970 --> 48:59.803
They will try to stop it,
but they will fail.

49:01.890 --> 49:04.097
The Caribbean corridor is closing forever.

49:04.270 --> 49:05.840
No one can change that.

49:07.730 --> 49:09.357
When that happens,
we will be the only way in.

49:09.440 --> 49:13.069
With your eastern network
repurposed for cocaine...

49:13.780 --> 49:15.190
fuck".

49:15.700 --> 49:17.315
we can take full advantage.

49:19.240 --> 49:20.286
What do you need?

49:20.490 --> 49:21.570
A union.

49:22.830 --> 49:26.288
More cocaine means more money.
A fucking monopoly.

49:26.540 --> 49:28.496
Where we set the terms.

49:29.090 --> 49:31.240
-More money means--
-The future.

49:33.470 --> 49:34.869
What about the past?

49:36.090 --> 49:37.216
For example,

49:37.760 --> 49:41.002
the thing with the agent, Camarena.

49:41.970 --> 49:44.347
I have a lot of people
on the other side of the border.

49:44.980 --> 49:48.268
They won't like me being
in business with...

49:49.480 --> 49:51.311
someone who killed one of theirs.

49:52.730 --> 49:53.810
What do I tell them?

49:55.650 --> 49:57.652
Tell them what everyone already knows...

49:59.370 --> 50:01.110
the men responsible are behind bars.

50:04.450 --> 50:07.248
That might work with people
who don't care about the truth.

50:07.330 --> 50:11.084
Tell them that there is more money
to be made.

50:11.170 --> 50:12.205
Money?

50:12.670 --> 50:13.705
Is that all?

50:15.220 --> 50:19.042
You have money, Miguel ngel.
I have money. They have money.

50:19.720 --> 50:21.756
You're talking about more money.

50:23.430 --> 50:25.227
At a cost that I'm not willing to pay.

50:27.140 --> 50:29.438
I'm sorry that you wasted your time.

50:29.520 --> 50:30.805
Sit down!

50:32.480 --> 50:35.142
You want to know what I need, right?

50:35.400 --> 50:37.527
Okay, then, I'll tell you, Don Juan.

50:38.030 --> 50:39.657
I need leverage.

50:41.910 --> 50:43.866
I saw what you wanted me to see.

50:43.950 --> 50:45.906
It's fucking great. What did you say?

50:46.000 --> 50:48.491
"The love and respect of his friends."

50:48.580 --> 50:51.663
The Americans put on a good show.
You have them in your pocket.

50:52.090 --> 50:53.455
Impressive.

50:54.550 --> 50:56.666
But don't act stupid, Don Juan.

50:58.180 --> 50:59.545
You're small-time.

51:04.100 --> 51:05.385
And so am I.

51:07.680 --> 51:08.840
You told me...

51:09.350 --> 51:12.513
that I brought my people, my federation,
out of the darkness.

51:14.020 --> 51:16.568
Well, that's true.
But the darkness is still there.

51:16.650 --> 51:19.357
And if the Colombians have their way,
we would slide back into it.

51:19.450 --> 51:22.408
All of us. You too. With all your friends.
Your people. Chopping each other to bits.

51:24.910 --> 51:27.037
This whole country is one step away
from chaos.

51:27.660 --> 51:31.414
A fucking free-for-all of independent
operators who think they can go it alone.

51:31.790 --> 51:34.167
And the Colombians love it.

51:35.210 --> 51:37.917
They would rather deal with us separately.

51:38.670 --> 51:42.003
Play us off of one another. Keep us under
their thumb by paying us slowly.

51:45.060 --> 51:50.225
We're middlemen to them.
Baggage handlers.

51:50.350 --> 51:52.181
We deliver their coke across
that fucking border

51:52.270 --> 51:54.682
to more Colombians waiting
on the other side

51:54.770 --> 51:56.647
so they can mark it up and sell it
for ten times the money.

51:58.110 --> 52:00.647
But we are the only ones
who can move their shit,

52:01.110 --> 52:03.192
so we should be able to rewrite the rules.

52:03.620 --> 52:05.690
It's time we tell them
how It's gomg to be.

52:12.750 --> 52:14.832
Finally, here's the man
I've been waiting to see,

52:15.040 --> 52:16.951
the man I've heard so much about.

52:18.800 --> 52:19.835
Very well.

52:20.220 --> 52:22.120
And this leverage?

52:22.220 --> 52:23.630
What would we do with it?

52:23.970 --> 52:26.803
We force them to start paying us
in cocaine. We get into retail.

52:28.720 --> 52:31.223
What'd I tell you, Juan?
This guy is a genius.

52:31.850 --> 52:33.511
Why would the Colombians let us do that?

52:33.600 --> 52:36.262
They won't have a choice.
Flix will have a monopoly.

52:36.480 --> 52:38.562
When they want to negotiate,

52:39.320 --> 52:41.390
fine, we'll negotiate.

52:42.320 --> 52:43.651
What would we ask for?

52:43.990 --> 52:45.867
We keep half the loads.

52:47.080 --> 52:49.287
And then we start selling it ourselves,
up north, using our people.

52:49.370 --> 52:51.702
How many Colombians in the States?

52:51.790 --> 52:53.246
No more than 800,000.

52:53.330 --> 52:54.536
And our people?

52:57.090 --> 52:58.796
At least 15 million.

53:03.220 --> 53:05.006
Well, I am impressed.

53:09.430 --> 53:12.012
I have to say,
I thought I had figured you out.

53:12.350 --> 53:14.341
You've surprised me, young man.

53:15.230 --> 53:16.094
I'm glad.

53:16.400 --> 53:17.685
Just one thing.

53:18.480 --> 53:20.107
You have a lot of enemies.

53:21.820 --> 53:22.809
I get it.

53:23.700 --> 53:28.148
But a man isn't defined by his enemies.
He is defined by his friends.

53:29.200 --> 53:30.360
His family.

53:31.040 --> 53:32.189
His people.

53:33.290 --> 53:34.609
From now on...

53:36.630 --> 53:38.200
my family is yours.

53:42.920 --> 53:43.966
Partners?

53:44.380 --> 53:48.134
I need a few weeks.
I want my people to hear It from me.

53:49.800 --> 53:51.256
But yes...

53:51.970 --> 53:53.221
partners.

53:55.270 --> 53:56.976
That's great. Right?

53:57.100 --> 53:58.306
We got it done.

54:11.330 --> 54:14.868
Get out of the way. Here I come.

54:15.870 --> 54:19.533
Long live love, motherfuckers!

54:33.010 --> 54:37.686
WELCOME HOME

54:38.020 --> 54:40.147
Love the sign, bro.

54:40.230 --> 54:41.390
Thank you.

54:41.650 --> 54:43.390
I did it myself.

54:43.480 --> 54:45.391
But you've gotta try this shit.

54:45.490 --> 54:47.105
It's called crack.

54:47.700 --> 54:49.156
Let me heat it up.

54:49.740 --> 54:52.447
I spent 18 months drinking wine
made in a toilet.

54:54.040 --> 54:55.439
Hey, my little witch.

54:56.450 --> 54:58.748
Welcome home, brother.

55:00.130 --> 55:01.199
Popeye.

55:03.960 --> 55:05.791
This is my man, David Barron.

55:05.880 --> 55:07.165
He's from San Diego.

55:07.590 --> 55:11.629
This motherfucker had my back
on the inside.

55:11.800 --> 55:12.960
He's family.

55:13.640 --> 55:15.596
Welcome to Tijuana, bro.

55:16.730 --> 55:18.095
So from San Diego?

55:18.180 --> 55:19.226
Logan Heights.

55:20.650 --> 55:22.720
Oh, shit. Take it.

56:05.320 --> 56:06.560
What the fuck are you doing here?

56:08.440 --> 56:09.566
Oh, Min...

56:09.990 --> 56:12.527
is that any way to greet an old friend?

56:13.780 --> 56:15.441
Come on, a kiss.

56:16.790 --> 56:20.078
-If somebody sees you...
-Nobody saw me, don't worry.

56:21.370 --> 56:22.530
What do you want?

56:29.880 --> 56:31.416
To talk business.

56:35.890 --> 56:37.596
Wipe that stuff off your face, Tigre.

56:45.150 --> 56:46.686
Get up. Get out of here.

56:51.860 --> 56:53.100
Assholes.

56:57.330 --> 56:58.479
Who are those guys?

56:58.580 --> 57:00.320
Sinaloan crew.

57:02.580 --> 57:04.070
Trash.

57:04.500 --> 57:07.128
Ramn! Hey, kid.

57:09.090 --> 57:10.125
What's up, Ramn?

57:11.510 --> 57:14.252
-What are you doing here?
-This is our club. We own it.

57:14.800 --> 57:15.960
You really didn't know?

57:16.680 --> 57:17.886
Owners?

57:19.140 --> 57:20.676
Oh, man. Thank God, bro.

57:20.770 --> 57:23.056
I was worried it was a gay club.

57:25.100 --> 57:26.761
Did you guys get my present?

57:26.860 --> 57:30.148
You motherfuckers keep our trucks all day,

57:30.690 --> 57:32.601
fucking up our business,

57:32.990 --> 57:34.560
and then you come here
and disrespect us

57:34.650 --> 57:38.063
on the day my brother is released
from prison? What the fuck?

57:38.410 --> 57:40.196
Hey, quiet.

57:40.290 --> 57:41.780
Shut the fuck up.

57:42.750 --> 57:44.706
We're sorry. We didn't know.

57:45.040 --> 57:46.325
You're right.

57:47.210 --> 57:50.919
Cheers to your family, your brother,
and his continued freedom.

57:51.250 --> 57:54.003
And I'm sorry about the pig.
It was a joke.

57:54.510 --> 57:56.046
You can send it back if you don't want it.

57:56.130 --> 57:57.085
I shot it.

57:59.470 --> 58:00.880
Can't take a joke.

58:02.310 --> 58:04.767
Some dogs only behave on the leash.

58:05.810 --> 58:07.141
Cheers, kid.

58:09.270 --> 58:10.567
All good?

58:11.360 --> 58:12.725
Got them on a leash.

58:13.570 --> 58:14.980
-All good?
-Yes.

58:15.070 --> 58:16.981
What's the problem? Let's party.

58:18.240 --> 58:20.231
I have some cocaine to move.

58:20.950 --> 58:22.486
I'd like to move it through your plaza.

58:25.410 --> 58:27.116
Talk to Miguel ngel.

58:27.710 --> 58:30.747
It's such a small amount.

58:30.920 --> 58:32.797
I don't think Flix even needs to know.

58:33.130 --> 58:35.337
Besides, I'd much rather pay you
for the privilege

58:35.420 --> 58:37.081
than someone who...

58:37.340 --> 58:38.580
has no faith in me.

58:40.430 --> 58:42.307
That is, unless you're scared.

58:45.890 --> 58:47.881
I heard he threw himself a birthday party.

58:48.100 --> 58:49.306
Didn't invite me.

58:50.650 --> 58:53.608
Made you all attend too.

58:54.070 --> 58:56.061
Like peasants.

58:56.150 --> 59:00.063
Bro, I think maybe
you should come downstairs.

59:02.080 --> 59:06.323
Look, the only reason Flix didn't kill me
for the move we made against him

59:06.660 --> 59:08.491
is because he still needs me.

59:11.080 --> 59:14.083
The only reason he didn't kill you...

59:16.970 --> 59:18.835
is because you don't matter
in the slightest to him.

59:21.390 --> 59:24.382
For your sake, I'm going to pretend
we never had this conversation.

59:25.390 --> 59:27.221
You can go out the way you came in.

59:27.310 --> 59:28.550
Don't let anyone see you.

59:57.380 --> 59:58.540
Bring the stretcher!

1:00:24.070 --> 1:00:25.480
We brought you a present.

1:00:26.160 --> 1:00:28.321
A toast, to your family.

1:00:28.450 --> 1:00:30.498
To blood and the ties which bond us.

1:00:31.000 --> 1:00:32.240
Cheers!

1:00:33.920 --> 1:00:36.206
And to Francisco Arellano Flix,

1:00:36.290 --> 1:00:38.292
who sucked more dicks than any inmate

1:00:38.380 --> 1:00:40.507
in the history of the California
prison system!

1:00:57.940 --> 1:00:59.146
What?

1:01:03.450 --> 1:01:04.815
Motherfucker!

1:01:56.170 --> 1:01:57.876
Welcome back, boss.

1:01:58.380 --> 1:01:59.495
It go well?

1:01:59.840 --> 1:02:01.705
It did. Very.

1:02:01.800 --> 1:02:03.085
Good.

1:02:03.460 --> 1:02:05.587
Did the
seora
eat yet?

1:02:05.680 --> 1:02:09.719
She took Amalia to Cuernavaca
for the night with some friends.

1:02:13.020 --> 1:02:13.975
Good.

1:02:14.770 --> 1:02:15.976
Can I get you anything?

1:02:16.600 --> 1:02:18.511
No, I'm good.

1:02:20.020 --> 1:02:21.647
Okay. Good night.
